FBIS3-56555 "drsov011_m_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Tajikistan Deputy Defense Minister Wounded, Driver Killed LD1801112194 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 1000 GMT 18 Jan 94 LD1801112194 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The car of Colonel Nurali Sheraliyev, deputy defense minister of the republic, was fire upon by unknown gunmen yesterday evening. Sheraliyev was returning to Dushanbe from the town of Nurek [80km south-east of Dushanbe]. The driver was killed and Colonel Sheraliyev and another person in the car were wounded as a result of the armed attack which took place between the towns of Nurek and Kofarnihon [25km south-east of Dushanbe]. The competent bodies have begun an investigation of the case. This was told to a correspondent of Khovar news agency by the reliable sources.
